 <quote>
  <cite>David Allen, <em>Getting Things Done: The Art of Stress-Free Productivity</em></cite>


  <p>Getting things done, and feeling good about it, means being willing to recognize, acknowledge, and appropriately manage all the things that have your consciousness engaged. Mastering the art of stress-free productivity requires it.</p>
</quote>
<p>Welcome to the <app>Getting Things GNOME!</app> user manual.</p> <p><app>Getting Things GNOME! (GTG)</app> is the task manager and organizer for the GNOME desktop environment that is inspired by the <em>Getting Things Done (GTD)</em> methodology.  It focuses on usability and simplicity.  <app>GTG</app> provides a simple, yet flexible organization tool for life and work.</p>

<p>For a quick introduction into both <app>GTG's</app> most basic features, as well as some advanced keyboard shortcuts, see <link xref="gtg-quickstart">Get Started</link> and <link xref="gtg-shortcut-keys">Shortcut Keys</link>. For details about <app>GTG's</app> interface, see <link xref="gtg-main-window">Understand GTG Main Window</link>.</p>

 <p>Other help topics are grouped together in the sections below. Enjoy using <app>Getting Things GNOME!</app></p>

